Description:
INTRODUCTION 
The Creation of RASCOM RASCOM is a Pan-African Satellite Communication Organization, created from the will of African Governments and States, and set up in order to bridge the digital divide between the continent and the rest of the world. 
To overcome the challenges of this digital divide and the opening up of rural areas in Africa, the member States of the African Unity (currently African Union) agreed to establish a satellite telecommunications system as part of an enhanced telecommunications network for Africa, intended to provide expanded telecommunications services to all African countries 
This manifest will of African Governments and States has led to the creation of the Regional African Satellite Communications Organization « RASCOM » following the adoption of the Resolution RASCOM/02 of the Conference of African Ministers responsible for Telecommunications held in May 1992 at Abidjan, Côte d’Ivoire.

MISSION
 Provide affordable infrastructure on a large scale to rural areas ; 
Develop and improve inter-urban communication ; 
Establish direct links between African countries ; 
Provide facilities for radio and television broadcast in African countries ; Support international connectivity ; 
Provide a range of services, voice, data, multi-media, telemedicine, tele-education, video conferencing etc.

OBJECTIVES
The main purpose of RASCOM shall be the design, development, construction, procurement, establishment, operation and maintenance of the space segment of the regional African telecommunications satellite system. In this context, RASCOM shall have as its prime objective the provision, on a commercial basis, of the space segment required for national and international public telecommunications services in Africa.

Stardome is a digital certification system. It is implemented through autonomous satellite CAs (certificate authorities) and certification modules embedded in third-party devices at data sources and their respective data processing points (read, control, modify and write), on the ground and on satellite, and through a blockchain for registration, attribution and validation of data and certificates.
The main functions fulfilled by Stardome are:
- to create, allocate and validate digital certificates using satellite CAs, recorded on a blockchain;
- to certify data at the source, through modules embedded in third-party devices and record them on a blockchain;
- to record these data through Stardome modules on a blockchain. This function is called "Chain of Custody".

O Grupo Century dedica-se ao avanço econômico e social em todas as regiões do Brasil, contando com mais de 70 anos de experiência no cenário tecnológico. Nossa atuação no mercado é marcada pela excelência em serviços relacionados a antenas parabólicas, receptores, conversores e outros produtos que integram o universo televisivo.

Comprometidos com altos padrões de qualidade, a SATBRAS Indústria Eletrônica da Amazônia Ltda., fabricante de produtos eletroeletrônicos, estabelece sua Política de Qualidade baseada nos seguintes princípios:

a) Buscamos incessantemente a satisfação de nossos clientes, colaboradores e demais partes interessadas;
b) Comprometemo-nos a atender aos requisitos legais inerentes ao nosso negócio, bem como aos requisitos estabelecidos por nossos clientes;
c) Investimos na capacitação e desenvolvimento contínuo de nossos colaboradores, reconhecendo a importância do capital humano para o sucesso da organização;
d) Promovemos melhorias constantes na eficácia dos processos do Sistema de Gestão da Qualidade, visando à otimização e à excelência operacional.

Nosso compromisso é fortalecer relações duradouras, contribuir para o desenvolvimento socioeconômico do país e manter a liderança no mercado tecnológico, sempre pautados pela qualidade e pela inovação.
